rename_snapshot(25.10)                                  rename_snapshot(25.10)

Name
       rename_snapshot - Allows you to rename existing snapshots

Syntax
       rename_snapshot

       [-help]

       [-branch <newBranch>]

       [-id <metricID>]

       [-name <newName>]

       -uuid <snapshotuuid>

       Allows you to rename existing snapshots.

       rename_snapshot  does not support canonical paths and cannot change the
       location of a snapshot within the hierarchy.

Parameters
       -branch <newBranch>
              Specifies the new branch for the snapshot.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each rename_snapshot parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man rename_snapshot

       -id <metricID>
              Specifies  the metric database ID to change. If you do not spec-
              ify any id, the tool will take current database as default.

              Data_type: string, optional

              Note: You can find the uuid of a snapshot  by  using  get_metric
              for the uuid metric.

       -name <newName>
              Specifies the new name for the snapshot. The tool will error out
              if you set the name to empty string.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -uuid <snapshotuuid>
              Specifies the snapshot UUID.

              The  tool  will  error out if there is no snapshot with the pro-
              vided uuid.

              Data_type: string, required

Related Information
              * get_metric

